# Agent execution behavior

## Before coding

Always:
- inspect nearby files first
- infer the current architecture from the actual repo
- reuse sound existing patterns
- identify all impacted layers before editing

## During coding

Prefer:
- the smallest correct change
- explicit models and state classes
- repositories and use cases for non-trivial flows
- pure functions for calculations and normalization
- defensive parsing and validation

Do not:
- make broad rewrites unless explicitly requested
- create half-implemented features that look complete
- invent API fields or DB columns silently
- leave call sites inconsistent after model changes

## After coding

Before stopping, verify:
- impacted imports are clean
- obvious dead code is removed
- state models still cover loading/error/content behavior
- business logic did not leak into UI
- tests were added/updated for non-trivial changes where practical

## Ambiguity handling

When requirements are incomplete:
- choose the most conservative maintainable interpretation
- leave an explicit TODO or assumption comment when genuinely necessary
- do not fabricate certainty

## Special rule for this product

For anything related to AI meal analysis:
- preserve editability
- preserve correction-first UX
- preserve trust signaling
- treat uncertainty as a real product concern, not a cosmetic one
